\ul Fire types\ulnone :\
Excel files are named according to the type of fire for which emissions are reported:\
TEMF: Temperate forest fires\
BORF: Boreal forest fires\
DEFO: Tropical deforestation fires\
DEGR: Tropical degradation fires (non-deforestation fires)\
ALLFOREST: all non-deforestation fires (TEMF + BORF + DEGR)\
\
Other fire types are available for extraction if needed: agricultural fires, peat fires and savanna fires.\
\
\'97\'97\'97\
\ul Pollutants\
\ulnone Each excel file contains one sheet per pollutant, each named with the pollutant acronym.\
The file GFED4_Emission_Factors.xlsx gives further details on these pollutants and their emission factors per gram of burned dry matter. \
List of pollutants: 
